caption: Edit: While the food is still good, the speed and order commitment time was lacking this past experience.  This restaurant is the byproduct of if Quizno's got their business model and nutrition right. All the subs are interesting products and they are all good. Why would you go to Jimmy John's or Subway when you can have better experiences here?
Better than the best.
Thus place is wonderful. From the art to the service and food just immaculate vibes. I'm not usually a sandwich person but when I had the Sensi Kush I fell in love. I highly suggest giving it a try.
The 5.0 was the bomb 💣 😍.
A place to eat the dopest sub sandwich after you smoke the dopest dope
Sandwiches are 🔥🔥

Had such a nice meal here that I had to make it my first google review! Cool and fun artwork on the wall and a creative menu. Their sandwiches can all be served on garlic bread, which I highly recommend. They also have wheat and white bread though.  With the purchase of a 8" sandwich I got a $3 Lagunitas IPA. Can't lose with that deal. Will definitely be returning in the near future
Melty gooey goodness comfort food. Even though it's a chain, they get it.
Fell in love when I visited in Colorado, stoked that it's here! Tasted just as good and fresh. Give me that white widow all daaaaay ♡
A great simple spot. Big delicious sandwiches. Smaller portions available too. Quick service and great people.

At first you are like “Is this too gimmicky to be good?” You could not be more wrong. The sandwich and service are incredible. I will definitely be back to try this entire menu. Highly recommend the white widow
Great sandwich shop

Huge fan of Cheba Hut Wicker Park!  I've tried about a dozen of their subs & am yet to have one that I didn't thoroughly enjoy.  My favorites are Midwest Best (be sure to add mayo), Orange Widow, Sensei Kush & Cali Mist.  If you are in the neighborhood give them a try you won't regret it!

Amazing hot sandwiches!  Not to mention, on of our sandwiches wasn't correct and when we called, one of the owners had the order remade and deliverd it himself. Talk about customer service :) Can't thank them enough! They've got our business.

everyone that works here seems like they actually like each other and have fun at work. its actually kind of entertaining to watch when waiting for my food. the food is always really good. I recommend getting a full sized sandwhich cuz you will def want that extra food later . my fave sandwhich rn is the sriracha one .

I have been to three Cheba Hut locations throughout the country and this one has to be my favorite due to the fact they perfectly toast their subs and the ratio of ingredients is on point. Only downside was I had to do pickup from here since the only delivery app I use is GrubHub.
Been to Denver and Madison so was stoked to see 1 open up locally. This may be my favorite location yet. Loved the mural inside too. No one out Cheba’s the Hut!
Easily one of the best subs I've had in Chicago and I've been here 17+ years. I will be a returning customer.

So, just ordered these dudes for the first time, and I really never leave reviews for places, but, they're the real deal. The AK-47 is about the best sandwiches I've had in a long time. Would gladly order from them once again.
Love this place but do check your order. Asked for mustard....got mushrooms lol.
Amazing staff and the food is Delicious!!
Such great flavor and friendly staff. Definitely one of my new favorite spots for a killer sandwich
Fye

We needed a good neighborhood place to grab a quick sub since there aren't many with vegetarian options nearby. Well this place makes awesome veggie subs! We've ordered from them multiple times now and we are hooked!
This place was very disappointing, let’s just say subway is way better..  one slice of meat and nothing but bread
This IS the place! Great tasting food and a friendly staff. Wonderful!
They ALWAYS forget my Buffalo sauce in my sandwich EVERY TIME 🥲
Amazing!

Too stoned to get your order right.  Placed order for Pickup in Nov,  was given completely wrong order plus missing the drink and dessert i purchased.  Spoke to manager Chris who said come in next time we'll comp your whole meal.  went back today, handed ORIGINAL receipt of Nov order and asked for duplicate order.  Rec'd Sandwich (tastes good, one star for that) but once again, omitted the beverage and the dessert.  Way too stoned to get it right.  Don't leave without double checking every 'ounce' of items in your bag.  Sigh.
Food is amazing as always. Delivery was a breeze with the CH app. Been a CH fan since 2005 when I was at ASU and am so excited to finally have it in my hometown!
Tasty sandwich shop with so many fun extras like nachos, hummus and amazing brownies. Love the full bar and outdoor seating! Appreciate all the veggie options, too.

The only negative thing I have to say is how close this location is to my apartment... excellent subs (have loved everything I have tried) and staff, a cool atmosphere and a bar. What else could you need?
I wish I had a pic, that Sriracha sandwich is the bomb

If I could give them 10 stars I would 🤩 This place was so awesome! I got the Panama red sandwich, garlic bread, pretzel bites and French onion soup. Everything was absolutely delicious and super fresh. I’m so excited to go here again! ❤️
Crazy delicious toasted sandwiches and salads. In spite of the stoner vibe, food is first-rate.
Has always been the go to while in CO and the ambience here made me feel like I was on Colfax.  Great theme and pretty much every meat sandwich is 🔥.

Hot tamale this place is the SPOT for tasty stoned delivery. The sandwiches are huge *and affordable* (all about getting the Acapulco Gold Au Jus!) And the desserts, especially their rotating cereal bar rice Krispy selection are a steal of a deal. Honestly, if you're in the delivery area, gotta try it AT LEAST once. :)
This place is awesome! Had the G-13 pinner and it was great! Oh and also the dirty hippie drink was just as good. Recommend to check it if you haven't yet.
5-0 sub was definitely good ! 😋
Fell in love with this place! It’s always busy so I had to stop in. Been back 3 times this week. Recommend the Kali Mist!!!
10 out of 10 would recommend, loaded not chos are straight fire. You have to get the not chos. Life changing experience.

Food is SICK, but the service is rough. There was an employee (short, Latinx) walking around with no mask on, and another staff (taller/black) man walking around with his nose sticking out of his mask handling food without gloves. The Latinx chick seemed to be done with her shift but man, watching her walk between the back, the kitchen, AND answering a patron’s question without her mask gave me goosebumps. Wait times for carry out orders are kind of absurd in the evenings as they don’t seem to yet have a fluid system for carry out orders made via online/phone call. Beautiful outdoor seating area, bar is awesome and generally the staff is pretty nice. Sandwiches have been on point 100% of the time. Writing this review as I wait for my gf waiting for her sandwich. It’s been 13 minutes of her waiting inside and we placed the order 15 minutes ago.
I would die for cheba hut
Good vibes, Good sammies, and cool atmosphere
Cali Mist sub and French onion soup
Delicious subs
Awesome sandwiches. Cool atmosphere. Definitely check it out.

Cheba Hut was my favorite place to order food in Iowa City and then they got rid of it. I moved back to Illinois last year and I am SOOOO excited that there’s a Cheba Hut here!!! The food options are unique, the theme is fun, and the service is quick and friendly.
Excellent service! Even better sandwiches! I've loved this place since I went in Arizona 20 years ago and couldn't wait to try it out here! Did not disappoint!!!
So happy to have this in Chicago! Amazing sandwiches 😍
Very fire 🔥 remember having this in Colorado
Hand's down-The best sub I ever had!
Good quick serve shop. Stoner murals and art inside are pretty cool. Would like to see larger drink size options. Owner was very friendly.
Great toasted sandwiches, reminds me of Potbelly but just a lot more options. I like that they have a bar as well. Pretty affordable as well.
Finally
One of the reasons I was so sad to move from Denver to Chicago last year was that there'd be no more Cheba Hut in my life but it's here now and my life is complete again

Finally a hot sandwich shop on division! Love these guys. Awesome people, excellent service and delicious toasted sandwiches. Haven't been inside yet but decor looks fun and inviting. Grabbed a sandwich right before close and they were out of there signature goo balls (highly recommend), so they refunded me and gave me a few other treats for free! Little things like that often go unnoticed but excellent service like that is priceless. I Look forward to some post covid (whenever that is) 1 am sammies!

I have been searching for a new, quality sandwich shop in Chicago and Cheba Hut is so good. The sandwiches are fun, really excellent, and so are some of the other accompaniments (pretzel bites and garlic cheese bread). I definitely recommend. I usually get this delivered via DoorDash and it’s always packaged excellently and arrives hot and fresh!
Mouth watering food, thirst quenching drinks, and a staff full of smiles. Definitely going back!!!
Love this place great food great vibes used to eat here a lot in Colorado glad they brought one to Chicago

We just had the most amazing experience here. It is my boyfriends thirty somethingth birthday and he found this place from a friend, so we took a chance.  The service was exceptional and each staff member including the owner made us feel special. They were super busy being a new hot spot especially for quick and efficient takeout service. We ended up sitting at the bar for about 3 hours and had some snacks, apps, and tasted drinks, then ordered dinner to go for later and I just finished it and I am now obsessed. We will be back time and time again and wish them and their friendly staff all the success in the world. Derek needed a special birthday and you delivered.  p.s. try any of their signature drinks or local drafts! great variety!

One of the best subs I've ever had. Every time I would travel to Colorado we visited Cheba Hut at least twice before heading back.  We've driven to Madison, Wisconsin for the subs (thats how good they are). I love all of the Cheba Huts, but being that I'm from Chicago, our mural is definitely my favorite. The atmosphere is dope too! From the food and drinks to the vibes- trust me, you have to check this place out!
Delicious subs. Reasonable prices. Traveled from the Southside to check them out. Wasn't disappointed

I have been a Cheba Hut customer for 20 years. They have the best sub sandwiches on the market. I'm so happy that Chris and Lance have brought a piece of my hometown to Chicago. Every sandwich is a must try.
Finally! I went to the location in Mesa, AZ religiously. Very exciting to have one open in my neighborhood.

My kids mostly, are the ones that turned me on to Cheba Hut, back in Mesa Arizona, right across the street from MCC, when we heard about this one opening in Wicker Park in Chicago we HAD to go and our sandwiches were fantastic!!! We Love Cheba Hut, and we drove from Elmhurst in the western suburbs, WELL worth it!! We will be back and often, its a clean organized beautiful restaurant, we Love Cheba Hut!!!!

Absolutely amazing on their first day in Chicago I've been to several in Arizona and it gives a complete unique Chicago Stoner vibe. The food tastes just like if I was at a cheba hut anywhere else which is the best part beside the Kool-Aid. Munchies were I'm point too  Dispensary agent approved
Cheba Hut is the best. All kinds of delicious hot subs on the menu.  This place is a can't miss lunch spot much welcomed in Chicago.

Delicious subs! My new fave sandwich spot. Everyone was super friendly, and the subs were great! I had the orange widow from the secret stash, and the white widow for my girlfriend. We love it and will always come back!
